        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <h2 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Next Steps</h2>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    Use this guide to systematically standardize .tt files across the project. 
                    Start with Phase 1 tasks in future sessions, following the established workflow for .tt file editing.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large); padding-top: var(--spacing-medium); border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
                <p>For technical support or questions about this standardization guide, contact the system administrator.</p>
                <p><em>This documentation is part of the Comserv system template standardization initiative.</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- 
TEMPLATE COMPLIANCE NOTES:

This standardization guide has been updated to be fully compliant with the documentation_tt_template.tt:

1. **META Block**: Complete with all required fields including TemplateType, page_version, last_updated, and site_specific
2. **PageVersion Format**: Updated to current standard with proper versioning
3. **Theme Compliance**: Uses CSS custom properties (--text-color, --header-font, etc.) for cross-theme compatibility
4. **Responsive Layout**: Uses .container, .row, .col-* grid system
5. **Color-Coded Blocks**: Info, success blocks with proper theme variable usage
6. **Documentation Category**: Properly categorized as "documentation" in META

This file serves as both a guide for standardization AND an example of a properly standardized .tt file.
-->